<br>
This was proposed as an enabler by Raz, for balance purposes.<br>
<br>
I don't believe it would be necessary, given the duration of fights, and our DPS relative to the DS, and also considering the effect of a slowed MOB. <br>
<br>
On the other hand it could act as a bargaining chip.<br>
<br>
Of course, all this is hypothetical anyway, since unfortunately there's not a &quot;Class Rep&quot; we can discuss this about at VI with any surety that our concerns would be listened to.<br>
<br>
Bara <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baramos1>Baramos1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 9:19:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Brainstorm: How to fix PoP Mage soloability</span><hr size=1> Let's see, what are some of the criteria we've talked about so far.  (Not <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>established</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but talked about.)<br>
<br>
I) VI concern:  Preserve Class Balance in terms of power.<br>
II) Other class concerns of relative worth and balance.  (&quot;Other Class Screaming&quot; Effect)<br>
III) Mage concerns: Preserve traditional aspects of soloing. <br>
<br>
Add more where I've left them out, or overlooked something.<br>
<br>
In the above list, I give items (I) and (II) more weight than (III) because I believe we should be able to think outside the box of our own past, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>to get something we desire</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  <br>
<br>
In other words, (III) is a reflection of my own resistance to change, while (I) and (II) are items I have the least influence over.<br>
<br>
Let's look at the proposals so far:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Increased HP and Defense for pets</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I) VI concern:  Preserve Class Balance?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
No.  With the increased HP and Defense, Mages could not only be dishing out nuclear DPS in groups, but they could also be sending Jobaber off to do some crowd control.<br>
<br>
Devil's Advocate:  So what, Mages were always able to do pet-mezing before.  Why not now?<br>
<br>
Rebuttal:  Yes, but Mages didn't have screaming DPS.  Adding pet mez on top of everything else they do is over-powering.<br>
<br>
Devil's Advocate:  Why do you keep saying that.  Mage DPS isn't really all that much higher, speaking from a scaling perspective.  All we've done is come closer to our old abilities, which is appropriate.<br>
<br>
Rebuttal: Even if that's true, and I'm not convinced, it's the perception that matters.  And perception now, by VI and Mages alike, is that DPS by Mages is sizzling.  This will soon become yet another Sacred Cow, and entrenched.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>II) Other class concerns of relative worth and balance.  (&quot;Other Class Screaming&quot; Effect)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Pets with huge HP and defense will cause an outcry.  Particularly HP, since it's so 'visible'.  <br>
<br>
Devil's Advocate: Well, maybe with HP, but what about defense?  Defense you cannot see, and if we could just up the defense of the pets to where it mitigates, avoids, or absorbs damage better, people wouldn't mind.<br>
<br>
Rebuttal:  I'm a Mage.  I don't know the particulars of defense.  It seems to me, however, that it doesn't scale linearly.  That is, tripling AC isn't going to decrease damage taken, by the same factor.  What would they have to do to pets in order to create a defensive scenario which would give us the desired effect?  Is it practical?  I don't know the answers to that.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>III) Mage concerns: Preserve traditional aspects of soloing.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
Yes, it would preserve the way we normally solo.  Pet gets in there.  We burn or re-pet as necessary.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Giving Mages Snare</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
Note:  I didn't put ROOT in here, because I feel that root is a different animal.  I regret putting root/snare together in earlier posts, as one.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I) VI concern:  Preserve Class Balance in terms of power</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Well, it depends on whether they deliberately removed our soloing ability, or whether it was merely an outgrowth of poor re-balancing, with regard to scaling.<br>
<br>
If they determined, &quot;Mages shall not solo&quot; then no, snare doesn't preserve class balance.<br>
<br>
However, I take the optimistic approach here, and say that it was an unintended side-effect.<br>
<br>
This skill doesn't allow us to &quot;pet mez&quot; in groups.  It doesn't allow us to &quot;ghetto mez&quot; with a root.  We wouldn't aggro kite in traditional trinity groups.  It doesn't add an overpowering Mage ability in raids.  It doesn't increase our DPS.  It doesn't keep a MOB from delivering damage.<br>
<br>
It preserves class balance.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>II) Other class concerns of relative worth and balance.  (&quot;Other Class Screaming&quot; Effect)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I can't think of a reason other snaring classes would be upset, too much. Snare is beneath the radar, in &quot;power terms&quot; generally speaking.<br>
<br>
Devil's Advocate:  Yeah but then Mages are gonna go off soloing too.  Yet another class leaving the melee to rot, as they go pump up their AA's solo.<br>
<br>
Rebuttal:  Mages have always been able to solo.  Have the last couple of months changed your grouping habits?<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>III) Mage concerns: Preserve traditional aspects of soloing.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
No.  Mages would be doing a different type of soloing, using the idea of kiting, as their Necro brethren do.<br>
<br>
Devil's advocate:  Mages could always aggro-kite, solo.  So Mages kite.<br>
<br>
Rebuttal: Not anymore. Not efficiently.<br>
<br>
Devil's Advocate:  I really don't want to kite.  I prefer traditional solutions.<br>
<br>
Rebuttal: Do you want to solo?  Not all change is bad.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>One-tick Slow</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I) VI concern:  Preserve Class Balance</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Again, caveat is that our inability to solo is an unintended side-effect.  (Half-full glass approach).<br>
<br>
No, a similar argument to the earlier HP and defense is appropriate here.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>II) Other class concerns of relative worth and balance.  (&quot;Other Class Screaming&quot; Effect)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I don't know.  Would Shaman be upset at a slow that didn't affect their slow?  Unsure.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>III) Mage concerns: Preserve traditional aspects of soloing</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. <br>
<br>
Yes, soloing would be much as it was before.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Better Pet healing</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I) VI concern:  Preserve Class Balance</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Yes, pet healing would be a drain on our mana pool, and we'd have less available mana with which to Burn.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>II) Other class concerns of relative worth and balance.  (&quot;Other Class Screaming&quot; Effect)</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I don't know.. would Clerics scream much about this?  I don't think they'd care.  Answer is unclear to me.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>III) Mage concerns: Preserve traditional aspects of soloing</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. <br>
<br>
Well, a purist would say no.  The lack of pet healing was once a Sacred Cow.  Happily, we got past that.  Now pet healing is acceptable, and according to many soloers styles nowadays, a pet heal is part of the solution.<br>
<br>
Looks like Snare, 1-tick-Slow, and Heals cause the fewest problems from a weighted analysis perspective.<br>
<br>
Snares and Heals come out &quot;ahead&quot; of 1-tick-slow, but our criteria are subjective enough to go either way.<br>
<br>
Even though it violates criterion (I), I really like that one-tick slow. =)  <br>
<br>
My <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>personal</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> opinion:<br>
<br>
While I like 1-tick-slow, I feel that criterion (I) is probably a prime consideration.  Overall power would increase quite a bit with that, and VI wouldn't like it.<br>
<br>
I don't like pet-healing as a matter of personal style.<br>
<br>
That leads me back to Snare as a second choice to 1-tick-slow.<br>
<br>
Edit: BTW, if you wanted to assign a numeric &quot;score&quot; to the above proposals, and weighting (I) at weight 3, weighting (II) at weight 2, and (III) at weight (1), and using the idea of go/no-go for point assignation, you get the following results:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Better Heals - 6<br>
Snare - 5<br>
Slow - 3<br>
HP/DEF - 1</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
